
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
	<meta name="robots" content="nofollow,noindex">
	<meta http-equiv="cache-control" content="no-cache">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no, minimal-ui">
	<style type="text/css">
		html, body { padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 11px; font-family: Tahoma, Verdana, "Geneva CE", Lucida, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #656565; }
		body { margin: 20px; background-color: #ffffff; }
		h1 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; margin-top: 10px; }
		h1 a { color: #004A80; text-decoration: none; }
		h1 a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
		p { margin-bottom: 20px; }
		p.error {  margin: 20px 0px; }
		p.error span { padding: 10px 20px; background-color: #FFEBEB; border: 1px solid #FFAFAF; color: #FF0000; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; }
		#logo { width: 200px; height: 80px; background: transparent url(data:image/gif;base64,) no-repeat 0px 0px; }
		#logo a { width: 100%; height: 70px; display: block; }
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div id="logo"><a href="/"></a></div>
	<h1><a href="/">FlashScore.com - First to deliver your scores!</a></h1>
	<p class="error"><span>Error: The requested page can't be displayed. Please try again later.</span></p>
</body>
</html>
